    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="97" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Motley</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 99.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 15, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I call your attention to the enclosed copy
                            of a despatch from M. A. Jackson, United States consul at Halifax, and
                            of an extract from a late Charleston paper, by which it was accompanied,
                            in regard to the proposed building in Europe of a number of fast-sailing
                            steamers for the purpose of running the blockade of Wilmington with
                            troops from Poland to the number of thirty thousand. You will exercise
                            your usual vigilance towards thwarting the scheme referred to.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Lothrop Motley</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Vienna.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
